updated.doc: Last modification time of the event (as a RFC 3339 timestamp). Read-only.

location.doc: Geographic location of the event as free-form text. Optional.

colorId.doc: The color of the event. This is an ID referring to an entry in the "event" section of the colors definition (see the "colors" endpoint). Optional.

creator.id.doc: The creator's Profile ID, if available.

creator.email.doc: The creator's email address, if available.

creator.self.doc: Whether the creator corresponds to the calendar on which this copy of the event appears. Read-only. The default is False.

organizer.id.doc: The organizer's Profile ID, if available.

organizer.email.doc: The organizer's email address, if available.

organizer.self.doc: Whether the organizer corresponds to the calendar on which this copy of the event appears. Read-only. The default is False.

start.date.doc: The date, in the format "yyyy-mm-dd", if this is an all-day event.

start.dateTime.doc: The time, as a combined date-time value (formatted according to RFC 3339). A time zone offset is required unless a time zone is explicitly specified in 'timeZone'.

start.timeZone.doc: The name of the time zone in which the time is specified (e.g. "Europe/Zurich"). Optional. The default is the time zone of the calendar.

end.date.doc: The date, in the format "yyyy-mm-dd", if this is an all-day event.

end.dateTime.doc: The time, as a combined date-time value (formatted according to RFC 3339). A time zone offset is required unless a time zone is explicitly specified in 'timeZone'.

end.timeZone.doc: The name of the time zone in which the time is specified (e.g. "Europe/Zurich"). Optional. The default is the time zone of the calendar.

recurrence[].doc: List of RRULE, EXRULE, RDATE and EXDATE lines for a recurring event. This field is omitted for single events or instances of recurring events.

recurringEventId.doc: For an instance of a recurring event, this is the event ID of the recurring event itself. Immutable.

originalStartTime.date.doc: The date, in the format "yyyy-mm-dd", if this is an all-day event.

originalStartTime.dateTime.doc: The time, as a combined date-time value (formatted according to RFC 3339). A time zone offset is required unless a time zone is explicitly specified in 'timeZone'.

originalStartTime.timeZone.doc: The name of the time zone in which the time is specified (e.g. "Europe/Zurich"). Optional. The default is the time zone of the calendar.

transparency.doc: Whether the event blocks time on the calendar. Optional. Possible values are:"opaque" - The event blocks time on the calendar. This is the default value."transparent" - The event does not block time on the calendar.

visibility.doc: Visibility of the event. Optional. Possible values are:"default" - Uses the default visibility for events on the calendar. This is the default value."public" - The event is public and event details are visible to all readers of the calendar."private" - The event is private and only event attendees may view event details."confidential" - The event is private. This value is provided for compatibility reasons.

iCalUID.doc: Event ID in the iCalendar format.

attendees[].id.doc: The attendee's Profile ID, if available.

attendees[].email.doc: The attendee's email address, if available. This field must be present when adding an attendee.

attendees[].displayName.doc: The attendee's name, if available. Optional.

attendees[].organizer.doc: Whether the attendee is the organizer of the event. Read-only. The default is False.

attendees[].self.doc: Whether this entry represents the calendar on which this copy of the event appears. Read-only. The default is False.

attendees[].resource.doc: Whether the attendee is a resource. Read-only. The default is False.

attendees[].optional.doc: Whether this is an optional attendee. Optional. The default is False.

attendees[].responseStatus.doc: The attendee's response status. Possible values are:"needsAction" - The attendee has not responded to the invitation."declined" - The attendee has declined the invitation."tentative" - The attendee has tentatively accepted the invitation."accepted" - The attendee has accepted the invitation.

attendees[].additionalGuests.doc: Number of additional guests. Optional. The default is 0.

attendeesOmitted.doc: Whether attendees may have been omitted from the event's representation. When retrieving an event, this may be due to a restriction specified by the 'maxAttendee' query parameter. When updating an event, this can be used to only update the participant's response. Optional. The default is False.

extendedProperties.private.key.doc: The name of the private property and the corresponding value.

extendedProperties.shared.key.doc: The name of the shared property and the corresponding value.

gadget.width.doc: The gadget's width in pixels. Optional.

gadget.height.doc: The gadget's height in pixels. Optional.

gadget.display.doc: The gadget's display mode. Optional. Possible values are:"icon" - The gadget displays next to the event's title in the calendar view."chip" - The gadget displays when the event is clicked.

anyoneCanAddSelf.doc: Whether anyone can invite themselves to the event. Optional. The default is False.

guestsCanInviteOthers.doc: Whether attendees other than the organizer can invite others to the event. Optional. The default is True.

guestsCanSeeOtherGuests.doc: Whether attendees other than the organizer can see who the event's attendees are. Optional. The default is True.

privateCopy.doc: Whether this is a private event copy where changes are not shared with other copies on other calendars. Optional. Immutable.

reminders.useDefault.doc: Whether the default reminders of the calendar apply to the event.

reminders.overrides[].method.doc: The method used by this reminder. Possible values are:"email" - Reminders are sent via email."sms" - Reminders are sent via SMS."popup" - Reminders are sent via a UI popup.

reminders.overrides[].minutes.doc: Number of minutes before the start of the event when the reminder should trigger.

endTimeUnspecified.doc: Whether the end time is actually unspecified. An end time is still provided for compatibility reasons, even if this attribute is set to True. The default is False.

locked.doc: Whether this is a locked event copy where no changes can be made to the main event fields "summary", "description", "location", "start", "end" or "recurrence". The default is False. Read-Only.

hangoutLink.doc: An absolute link to the Google+ hangout associated with this event. Read-only.
